 - [ ] Self-contained code example attached
 - [X] Critical issue

Hi

I've some predefined structs with std::string/CString members like

```struct Foo
{
  int i; 
  std::string str;
  CString cstr;
} 
```

What does the UA_DataTypeMembers have to look like in order to encode/decode it correctly as strings ?

```
{
   UA_TYPENAME("i").           /* .memberName */
   &UA_TYPES[UA_TYPES_INT32],  /* .memberType */
   0,                          /* .padding */
   false,                      /* .isArray */
   false.                      /* .isOptional */
},
{
   UA_TYPENAME("str").         /* .memberName */
   &UA_TYPES[UA_TYPES_???],    /* .memberType */
   0,                          /* .padding */
   false/true?,                /* .isArray */
   false.                      /* .isOptional */
},
{
   UA_TYPENAME("cstr").        /* .memberName */
   &UA_TYPES[UA_TYPES_???],    /* .memberType */
   0,                          /* .padding */
   false/true?,                /* .isArray */
   false.                      /* .isOptional */
}
```
thx in advance !

